Borja Delgado captured a rare sight while skiing on the Pyrenees. Storm Celia initially brought the dust from the Sahara Desert to southern Spain, where authorities advised residents to wear masks and avoid being outside for long periods. The phenomenon has also affected parts of France, Portugal, UK and as far as Germany. (All photos are via CFP) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)